  "prompt": "When the Night King's White Walkers take children, do they become fully grown like those at end of the Game of Thrones episode \"Oathbreaker?\"",
  "response": "In \"Game of Thrones,\" it is implied that the White Walkers have the ability to transform human infants into White Walkers themselves, as seen when Craster's male children are offered to them. In the series, there is a scene where the Night King touches the cheek of a baby, presumably transforming him into a White Walker. However, the show does not provide detailed information on the growth process of these children after transformation.\n\nBy the time we see the White Walkers in action, they appear as fully grown adults, but the specifics of how quickly they grow or mature after being transformed are not explained in the series. It remains one of the many mysteries within the lore of \"Game of Thrones\" that hasn't been fully explored, either in the show or in the original \"A Song of Ice and Fire\" books by George R.R. Martin.",
